-- Davy Said to Sell 5 Million Ryanair Shares for Chief Executive O'Leary
-- Steven Rothwell
-- 2010-07-27T14:40:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/davy-said-to-sell-5-million-ryanair-shares-for-chief-executive-o-leary.html

          
          
             Ryanair Holdings Plc’s Chief
Executive Officer Michael O’Leary sold 5 million shares in
Europe’s largest discount airline, according to a person
familiar with the transaction.  
 Davy Stockbrokers placed the shares at 3.90 euros apiece,
according to the person, who declined to be identified. Stephen
McNamara, a spokesman for Ryanair, said the company doesn’t
comment on the personal dealings of O’Leary.  
 The stock dropped 9.6 cents, or 2.4 percent, 3.95 euros at
3:37 p.m. in Dublin.  
          
          


  


        